sentence:
• The Procter & Gamble Company's ( PG ) shares gained 2.9% after announcing fiscal first quarter adjusted earnings per share of $0.98, beating the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $0.94
• Shares of Whirlpool Corp. ( WHR ) plunged 8.7% after reporting that a stronger dollar led to lower third quarter revenues of $5,277 million, lower than the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $5,320 million
• Capital One Financial Corporation's ( COF ) shares jumped 8.3% after declaring third quarter earnings per share from continuing operations of $1.99 per share, outpacing the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $1.92
• Shares of Twitter, Inc. ( TWTR ) rose 3.9% after company's CEO Jack Dorsey said he will contribute 6.8 million Twitter's shares, worth around $200 million, from his holding for Twitter's employees
